==== gedit 2.12.1 ====

==== gedit 2.12.0 ====

==== gedit 2.11.93 ====

2005-08-29  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* dialogs/gedit-dialog-replace.c
	(replace_dlg_replace_button_pressed): use converted_search_string instead
	of search_string when calling g_utf8_caselessnmatch. Do not leak
	converted_search_string

2005-08-26  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixed bug #166189: Encoding should not be remembered when auto-detected
	
	* gedit-document.c (update_document_contents)
	(gedit_document_set_uri) (gedit_document_save_as)
	(gedit_document_get_encoding): merged set_encoding and set_uri, do not
	remember encoding in metadata when encoding has been auto-detected.

==== gedit 2.11.92 ====

==== gedit 2.11.91 ====

2005-08-08  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	gedit-mdi-child.c: fix runtime warning due to recent-files api
	breakage.

2005-08-05  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixed bug #101281: [ui-review] Undo preference dialog

	Based on a patch by Michael Terry <mike@mterry.name>

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences-dialog.c (setup_editor_page)
	(get_preferences_dialog): removed code releated the the "Undo" 
	preferences

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences.glade2: removed "Undo" preferences

	* gedit-prefs-manager.h: updated to reflect changes to gedit.schemas.in

==== gedit 2.10.4 ====

2005-08-04  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* bonobo-mdi.c (bonobo_mdi_update_child): update the Documents menu too

2005-08-03  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-document.c (get_uri_shortname_for_display): cleaned up

	Fixed bug #137539: recent files menu broken with very long file names.

	* recent-files/*: sync to libegg. 

2005-08-03  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-view.c: workaround gtktextview scrolling bug. bug #172277.

2005-08-03  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-mdi.c (tooltip_func): ellipsize the URI if needed.

2005-08-01  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-mdi.c (open_button_pressed_cb): ellipsize the recent list
	in the tool item.

2005-08-01  Ruben Vermeersch  <ruben@Lambda1.be>

	Fixed bug #309187 (Preselected highlighting mode in preferences)
	
	* dialogs/gedit-preferences-dialog.c setup_syntax_highlighting_page): 
	Automatically select the language of the active document.

2005-08-01  Guillaume Desmottes <cass@skynet.be>

	Fixed bug #308237 (sort the languages list alphabetically)

	* gedit-languages-manager.h: new function
	gedit_languages_manager_get_available_languages_sorted
	
	* gedit-languages-manager.c: new functions
	gedit_languages_manager_get_available_languages_sorted
	and language_compare. Add two global variables: languages_list 
	and languages_list_sorted
	
	* gedit-mdi.c: use gedit_languages_manager_get_available_languages_sorted
	instead of gtk_source_languages_manager_get_available_languages
	
	* dialogs/gedit-preferences-dialog.c: ditto

2005-08-01  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* recent-files/*: sync to libegg.

2005-08-01  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-tooltips.c (gedit_tooltips_force_window): enable 
	ellipisization

	* gedit-utils.c (gedit_utils_str_middle_truncate): fixed to be
	UTF-8 compliant.

2005-07-29  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixed bug #306847 (RFE: conversion option for CP932, EUC_JP_MS)

	* gedit-encodings.c: added CP932 and EUC_JP_MS to the list
	of known encodings. 
	Patch by Kazuhiko Maekawa <Kazuhiko.Maekawa@Sun.COM>

2005-07-28  Paolo Maggi <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixed bug #166903 (this fix has been backported from the
	new_mdi branch).

	* gedit-document.c (get_uri_shortname_for_display)
	(update_uri_for_display): new functions
	(gedit_document_finalize): free new variables uri_for_display 
	and short_name_for_display
	(gedit_document_get_raw_uri): removed "const" 
	(gedit_document_get_uri): rewritten
	(gedit_document_get_short_name): ditto
	(gedit_document_set_uri): call update_uri_for_display
	(gedit_document_get_mime_type): removed "const".

	* gedit-document.h: removed some "const *" from prototypes.

2005-07-27  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@ximian.com>
 
 	Fixes bug #311187:
 
 	* gedit-file-selector-util.c (gedit_file_selector_save): Take a
 	full URI instead of a basename for "default_filename"; actually,
 	renamed this argument to "default_uri".
 	(run_file_selector): Likewise.
 	(create_gtk_selector): Likewise.  Also, just call
 	gtk_file_chooser_set_uri() with the default_uri if it is
 	available.
 
 	* gedit-file.c (gedit_file_save_as): Use the document's raw URI if
 	we already have it and it is a file:/// URI --- don't split into
 	dirname and basename.

2005-07-23  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-debug.h: fix printing the function name.

2005-07-23  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-utils.c: use gtk_button_set_image to build custom buttons.

2005-07-22  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-prefs-manager.c (gconf_client_get_string_with_default):
	fixed bug #303943 (gedit crash). We were executing "*err = error" with
	err = NULL.

2005-07-22  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-view.c: do not scroll on copy.

2005-07-13  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-prefs-manager.c: init unitialized variable, spotted
	by David Binderman.

	* gedit-metadata-manager.c: backport Paolo Maggi's fix from
	new_mdi so that the timeout callback is not stopped.

==== gedit 2.10.3 ====

2005-06-08  Ray Strode  <rstrode@redhat.com>

	* gedit-file-selector-util.c: (replace_dialog):

	* gedit-file.c: (gedit_file_revert_dialog):
	(gedit_file_open_from_stdin):

	* gedit-io-error-dialogs.c: 
	(gedit_error_reporting_loading_file):
	(gedit_error_reporting_reverting_file):
	(gedit_error_reporting_saving_file):
	(gedit_error_reporting_creating_file):

	* gedit-utils.c: (gedit_warning): add "%s" as
	format string to message dialog functions

	Pass format string to message dialog functions (bug 306800).

2005-06-06  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* dialogs/gedit-close-confirmation-dialog.c: make labels
	selectable. Patch by David A Knight.

==== gedit 2.10.2 ====

2005-04-04  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit2.c (gedit_handle_automation): does not free data and
	data->file_list before reading them.

2005-04-04  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit2.c: fix leak in yesterday's focus patch.

2005-04-03  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* dialogs/gedit-encodings-dialog.c: mark var as static, patch by
	Benoît Dejean.

2005-04-03  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-window-server.c:
	* gedit2.c: fix focus for the second and successive instances.

2005-04-03  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-application-server.c:
	* bonobo-mdi.c: make sure that active_window is set appropriately.

2005-04-03  Benoît Dejean  <TazForEver@dlfp.org>

	* gedit-languages-manager.c: (string_to_tag_style): Fixed a leak.

2005-04-02  Benoît Dejean  <TazForEver@dlfp.org>

	* gedit-document.c: (gedit_document_save_as_real):
	* gedit-print.c: (save_gedit_print_config_to_file): Fixed write () usage.
	write () returns a ssize_t which is signed.
	
	* gedit-mdi.c: (get_dirname): Removed unneeded and unsafe
	g_return_val_if_fail ().

==== gedit 2.10.1 ====

2005-03-25  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit/GNOME_Gedit.idl:
	* gedit/gedit-window-server.c:
	* gedit/gedit2.c:

	Always open a new document if the current one is not untouched.

2005-03-08  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit/GNOME_Gedit.idl:
	* gedit/bonobo-mdi.c:
	* gedit/gedit-application-server.c:
	* gedit/gedit-utils.c:
	* gedit/gedit-utils.h:
	* gedit/gedit2.c:

	When launching gedit check if there is already a gedit window on the 
	current workspace: if yes, open the the document there, otherwise 
	create a new window.

==== gedit 2.10.0 ====

==== gedit 2.9.7 ====

2005-02-27  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-document.c (update_document_contents): fixes bug #167867 (Autosave
	should not save unmodified files). Call gedit_document_set_readonly after
	gedit_document_set_uri to activate autosaving also if the document has never
	been saved before.

	* gedit-encodings.c (gedit_encoding_to_string)
	(gedit_encoding_get_charset) (gedit_encoding_get_name): fixes some
	broken preconditions

2005-02-26  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-mdi.c: be smarter about ellipsizing the window title when
	the filename is very long.

2005-02-23  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit2.c (main): fix small leak.

2005-02-21  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* GNOME_Gedit.idl:
	* gedit-document-server.c:
	* gedit-window-server.c (impl_gedit_window_server_openURIList): pass
	the encoding specified on the command line.

2005-02-21  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixes bug #167874: Specify the line number on the command line is broken
	
	* GNOME_Gedit.idl: added line_pos argument to openURIList

	* bonobo-mdi.[ch] (bonobo_mdi_add_views): added set_view argument, if
	set_view is TRUE,  sets as active the first added view

	* gedit-document-server.c
	(impl_gedit_document_server_setLinePosition): goes to the right line

	* gedit-document.c (gedit_document_class_init): uses G_SIGNAL_RUN_FIRST 
	for the "loaded" signal
	(gedit_document_real_loaded):  places cursor at line 0
	when the document is loaded.

	* gedit-file.c: added the "first" field to the UriToLoad struct, new
	static variables first_document and active_doc_reused
	(document_loaded_cb): removed a call to 
	gedit_document_goto_line 
	(open_files_done): for the first document, moves the cursor to the 
	requested  line 
	(open_files): initialize first_document and active_doc_reused
	(gedit_file_open_uri_list): set the value of the first field of UriToLoad

	* gedit-view.c (gedit_view_expose): new function, scrolls to "insert"
	on the first expose
	(gedit_view_new): does not scroll to "insert", connect the "expose-event"
	signal
	(move_cursor)(gedit_view_cut_clipboard) (gedit_view_copy_clipboard)
	(gedit_view_paste_clipboard) (gedit_view_delete_selection)
	(gedit_view_scroll_to_cursor): uses gtk_text_view_scroll_to_mark with
	margin set to GEDIT_VIEW_SCROLL_MARGIN (0.02) instead of 
	gtk_text_view_scroll_mark_onscreen, this should improve a bit the way
	gedit scrolls text when searching for text

	* gedit-window-server.c (impl_gedit_window_server_openURIList): added
	line_pos argument

	* gedit2.c (gedit_load_file_list): manages the case in which "gedit +line"
	with no files on the command line is called
	(gedit_get_command_line_data): goes to the last line when of the file
	"gedit + file" is called
	(gedit_handle_automation): use the new GNOME_Gedit_Window_openURIList
	prototype

2005-02-12  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* dialogs/close_all_dialog.glade2: removed from CVS since it is 
	unused and not distributed.

2005-02-12  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-view.c: refresh ln and col only when the insert mark
	is moved. Speeds up search and replace.

2005-02-08  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit2.c: use icon from the icon theme.

==== gedit 2.9.6 ====

2005-02-07  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixed bug #122433: Alt+N shortcut does not select correct tab

	* bonobo-mdi.c (child_list_activated_cb): uses view instead of child
	(child_list_menu_add_item_from_view): new function
	(child_list_menu_create): uses views instead of children
	(child_list_menu_remove): ditto (child_list_menu_create_all)
	(book_button_release) (bonobo_mdi_move_view_to_new_window)
	(book_create) (app_create) (bonobo_mdi_add_view_real)
	(bonobo_mdi_add_views) (bonobo_mdi_add_toplevel_view)
	(bonobo_mdi_remove_view): call child_list_menu_remove_all and
	child_list_menu_create_all
	 (bonobo_mdi_add_child)	(bonobo_mdi_remove_child): don't call
	child_list_menu_remove_all and child_list_menu_create_all

	Thanks to Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com> for the first 
	version of the patch.

2005-02-03  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* recent-files/* : update from libegg.

2005-02-01  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-menus.c: fix thinko in my escape slashes patch.

2005-02-01  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit2.c:
	* gedit-metadata.[ch]: lazy init for the metadata.

2005-02-01  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit2.c (gedit_set_default_icon): uses 
	gtk_window_set_default_icon_from_file instead of 
	gnome_window_icon_set_default_from_file
	(main): sets the activation env to the canonical DISPLAY value,
	fixes bug #157147 (per display registration fails if DISPLAY 
	env is not complete)

2005-01-27  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-mdi.c: plug small memory leak.

2005-01-27  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-menus.c: escape slashes from bonobo menus to fix potential
	crash
	* gedit-mdi.c: use g_string_sized_new for the escaping functions.

2005-01-25  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-convert.[ch] (gedit_convert_from_utf8): returns the size of
	the converted text (as number of bytes)
	
	* gedit-document.c (gedit_document_save_as_real): fixes 
	bug #156423 (Saving in UTF-16 encoding destroys files)

2005-01-25  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixed bug #115070 (RFE: usability: <esc> shoud close Search dialog)

	Since nothing seems to change on the HIG side, I have decided 
	that gedit will 'take the lead' on this problem and so, 
	I have enabled ESC to close the search/replace dialog and the 
	"go to line" one.

	* gedit/dialogs/gedit-dialog-goto-line.c
	(dialog_goto_line_get_dialog): close the dialog when the ESC button
	is pressed

	* gedit/dialogs/gedit-dialog-replace.c (dialog_replace_get_dialog)
	(dialog_find_get_dialog): ditto

2005-01-23  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* recent-files/egg-recent-item.c (egg_recent_item_get_short_name):
	fix segfault.

2005-01-19  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-io-error-dialogs.c: fix typos in error messages.

2005-01-14  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-view.c: also change the cursor color when changing the text 
	color. (#119922)

2005-01-12  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-mdi-child.c (set_tooltip): use g_markup_printf_escaped instead
	of g_strdup_printf

2005-01-12  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixed bug #161612 (Use of "Home" key when text editing)

	* gedit-view.c (move_cursor) (gedit_view_move_cursor): new functions
	(gedit_view_init): connect the move-cursor signal to 
	gedit_view_move_cursor

==== gedit 2.9.4 ====

2005-01-11  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* recent-files/egg-recent-model.c (end_element_handler)
	(text_handler): locally fixes bug #160531 (startup takes ages)

2005-01-11  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Based on a patch by Juerg Billeter <j@bitron.ch>
	
	* dialogs/gedit-preferences-dialog.c
	(bracket_matching_checkbutton_toggled) (setup_view_page)
	(get_preferences_dialog): added new "Highlight Matching Bracket" option

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences.glade2: ditto

	* gedit-document.c (gedit_document_init): ditto

	* gedit-prefs-manager-app.c (gedit_prefs_manager_app_init)
	(gedit_prefs_manager_bracket_matching_changed): ditto

	* gedit-prefs-manager.c: ditto

	* gedit-prefs-manager.h: ditto

2005-01-10 Naveen & Team < naveenchandranv@gmail.com >

	* Fixed bug #161998 (http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=161998).
	Save Confirmation dialog is now HIG compliant.
	The "Don't Save" button has been changed to "Close without Saving".

2005-01-10  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* recent-files/egg-recent-model.c: sync to latest
	libegg.

2005-01-08  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences-dialog.c
	(highlight_current_line_checkbutton_toggled) (setup_view_page)
	(get_preferences_dialog): added new "Highlight Current Line" option

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences.glade2: ditto

	* gedit-prefs-manager-app.c (gedit_prefs_manager_app_init)
	(gedit_prefs_manager_hl_current_line_changed): ditto

	* gedit-prefs-manager.c: ditto

	* gedit-prefs-manager.h: ditto

	* gedit-view.c (gedit_view_init): ditto

2005-01-07  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-commands.c (gedit_cmd_help_about): replace "translator_credits" with
	"translator-credits" (as requested in bug #150106:Modules should use 
	"translator-credits" intead of "translator_credits"). Added comment for 
	translators.

2004-12-13  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences.glade2: s/Tabs/Tab Stops and 
	s/Tabs width/Tab width  and added a comment for translators (fixes 
	bug #131419: l10n: Refer to tabulators as "tabulators", not "tabs".)

2004-12-13  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	Fixed bug #130748: Auto save settings are not reflecting immediately

	* gedit-document.c (gedit_document_init)
	(gedit_document_set_readonly) (gedit_document_real_loaded)
	(gedit_document_auto_save)(gedit_document_save) 
	(gedit_document_save_as):  use new auto_save and auto_save_interval 
	member variable. 
	(gedit_document_enable_auto_save): new function 
	(gedit_document_set_auto_save_interval): new function 
	(gedit_document_load_from_stdin): fixed a "typo" while checking the encoding

	* gedit-document.h: Added prototype for	gedit_document_enable_auto_save (), 
	and gedit_docuent_set_auto_save_interval ().

	* gedit-prefs-manager-app.c (gedit_prefs_manager_app_init)
	(gedit_prefs_manager_auto_save_changed): notifies when auto save is 
	enabled and/or auto save interval is changed.
	(gedit_prefs_manager_undo_changed): fixed a mem leak

2004-12-13  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences-dialog.c (setup_editor_page): check for the 
	validity of the auto_save interval.

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences.glade2: s/auto indentation/automatic indentation

2004-12-13  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit2.c: do not process further options if --quit is specified.

2004-12-10  Balamurali Viswanathan  <balamurali.viswanathan@wipro.com>

	Patch from Srirama Sharma  <srirama.sharma@wipro.com>

	* dialogs/uri.glade2: Remove the explicit call to set AtkRelation 
	since the widget is set as mnemonic widget. Fixes the Bug #160593.

2004-12-07  Arvind Samptur  <arvind.samptur@wipro.com>

	Patch from Srirama Sharma  <srirama.sharma@wipro.com>

	* gedit/dialogs/gedit-page-setup-dialog.c: Setting the AtkRelation 
	explicitly for the mnemonic widget is causing gnopernicus to read 
	the label thrice. Hence removing the explicit declaration will fix the Bug #160322.

2004-12-06  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-document.[ch]: store the myme_type in Document->priv.
	* gedit-mdi-child.c: use the above instead of refetching it.

2004-12-06  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-io-error-dialogs.c: add error message for the case were the
	file we are trying to open is not a regular file.

2004-12-05  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-document.c: do not create unwanted backups in autosave mode.

2004-12-05  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-view.c (gedit_view_update_cursor_position_statusbar): added a comment
	for translators (see bug #104439 for more info).

2004-12-05  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-file.c:
	* dialogs/gedit-close-confirmation-dialog.c: fix a ngettext string.

2004-12-05  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-io-error-dialogs.[ch]:
	* gedit-utils.[ch]:
	* gedit-file.c:
	* Makefile.am:

	Split error dialogs for io operations in a separate file.

2004-12-02  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-mdi.c: delay the recent view creation for the toolbar
	button to the first button press. Should improve startup time.

2004-11-28  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* gedit-languages-manager.c: mark a global var as static.

2004-11-25  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* dialogs/gedit-preferences-dialog.c: do not leak tooltips.

2004-11-21  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	dialogs/gedit-encodings-dialog.glade2: remove separator.
	dialogs/gedit-encodings-dialog.c: use g_slist_find instead of
	reimplementing it.

2004-11-21  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	dialogs/gedit-plugin-manager.c: use gtk_tree_model_get_iter_first
	instead of the deprecated gtk_tree_model_get_iter_root.

2004-11-18  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* GNOME_Gedit.idl:
	* gedit-document-server.c:
	* gedit-document.[ch]: remove more unused functions.

2004-11-18  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* dialogs/gedit-dialog-replace.c: use gtk api to handle selection.
	* gedit-document.[ch]: remove unused functions.

2004-11-18  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* GNOME_Gedit.idl:
	* gedit-document-server.c: remove unused methods from the doc server.

2004-11-17  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* plugins-engine.c: use gkeyfile instead of deprecated
	gnome-icon-theme to parse plugin files.

2004-11-17  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* dialogs/gedit-dialog-goto-line: include stdlib to fix atoi warning.

2004-11-15  Paolo Borelli  <pborelli@katamail.com>

	* dialogs/gedit-close-confirmation-dialog.c: free selected_documents 
	list in finalize.

2004-11-15  Paolo Maggi  <paolo@gnome.org>

	* gedit-commands.c (gedit_cmd_help_about): updates my email address

